bcl:definition.bcl:text:
regulatory body institution class has the same
        meaning as in section 1 of the Fees and Student Tuition Protection Fund
        Regulation;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
ends on the date the institution's certificate expires as
                            determined under section 72 (4) [transition — registration and
                                accreditation] of the Act;

bcl:definition.bcl:text:
student enrolment contract has the same meaning as
        in section 1 of the Fees and Student Tuition Protection Fund
        Regulation;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
a copy of the student enrolment contract used by the institution
                            for approved programs of instruction and for programs of instruction
                            that do not require approval;

2.5% if the institution's most recent financial statements
                            provided to the registrar, or to the former registrar, show a debt ratio
                            of less than 0.2;
